<p><img src="https://stmargarets.london/assets/images/2020/st-mags-station.jpg" width="150" align="right" style="border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 1px;" alt="" /></p>

<p>South Western Railway passengers face four more days of strikes after the Rail, Maritime and Transport Union (RMT) has voted to strike in March.  The upcoming strikes follows a stretch of 27 days of strikes in December and is the sixth time in the past two and a half years that the union has voted for industrial action.  The strike will last from 10:00 on 9 March and 09:59 on 10 March and then again between 10:00 on 12 March and 09:59 on 13 March.</p>

